And, in saying this, I do not mean that art cannot in some cases give polish,-——for well I know that good abilities may through instruction become better, and that such as are not of the best can nevertheless be, in some measure, quickened and amended—‚ but there are some men either so tongue- tied, or so discordant in tone, or so wild and boorish in feature and gesture, that, even though sound in talent and in art, they yet cannot enter the ranks of the orators.
